    "name": "Yarn",
    "slug": "yarn",
    "definitions": [
      {
        "source": "SMI",
        "text": "The notice of yarn is contained in an extremely obscure passage in (1 Kings 10:28; 2 Chronicles 1:16) The Hebrew Received Text is questionable. Gesenius gives the sense of “number” as applying equally to the merchants and the horses: “A band of the king’s merchants bought a drove (of horses) at a price.”"
      }
